obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (68853)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title Interpretation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284&sectionId=68853&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `The following words and expressions in this Act shall have the meanings hereby`
  line `assigned to them, unless there be something in the subject or context repugnant to such construction (that`
  line `is to say),`
  line
  line `“Magistrate.” — The word Magistrate shall include all persons, within their respective`
  line `jurisdictions, exercising all or any of the powers of a Magistrate;`
  line
  line `“Subordinate.”—The word “Subordinate,” as applied to Police functionaries, shall mean`
  line `District Superintendents and their Assistants.`
  line
  line `“Police.”—The word “Police” shall include General and Village Police, Cuttoobadies,`
  line `Kavilgars, and all other persons, by whatever name known, who exercise any Police functions`
  line `throughout the Madras Presidency.`
  line
  line `“General Police District.”— The expression General Police District shall embrace all districts`
  line `to which the operation of this Act shall be extended;`
  line
  line `“Property.” — The word property shall include any movable property, money or valuable`
  line security;
  line
  line `Number.—Words importing the singular mumber shall include the plural number, and words`
  line `importing the plural number shall include the singular number.`
  line
  line `Gender.—Words importing the masculine gender shall include females.`
  line
  line `“Person.”—The word “person” shall include company or corporation.`
  line
  line `“Month.”—The word “month” shall mean calendar month.`
  line
  line `“Cattle.”— The word cattle shall, besides horned cattle, include elephants, camels, horses,`
  line `asses, mules, sheep, goats and swine`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (68854)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title `Laws repealed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284&sectionId=68854&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `The several Regulations and Acts mentioned in the Schedule hereunto annexed`
  line `are hereby repealed and amended to the extent and in the manner therein set forth, within the limits of the`
  line `General Police District; except so far as they repeal the whole or any part of any other Regulation or Act,`
  line `and except as to any act or offence which shall have been done or committed, or to any fine or penalty`
  line `which shall have been incurred or to any proceedings which shall have been commenced, before this Act`
  line `shall come into operation :`
  line `Proviso. Provided also that nothing in this Section shall be construed to affect`
  line `any judicial function or jurisdiction original or appellate, which by any existing law may be exercised by`
  line `any of the Officers mentioned in the enactments above repealed.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (68855)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Jurisdiction of Officers appointed under Regulation XI, 1816.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284&sectionId=68855&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `Nothing contained in this Act`
  line `shall affect the powers of appointment given to Magistrates by Section XL of Regulation XI. 1816 of the`
  line `Madras Code or the jurisdiction or functions of Officers appointed under such powers, save only that no`
  line `Officer so appointed shall be competent to exercise any of the functions or duties of Executive Police`
  line Officers.
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (68856)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Superintendence vested in Governor in Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284&sectionId=68856&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `The superintendence of the police`
  line `throughout the General Police District shall vest in, and be exercised by the Governor in council, and,`
  line `except as authorized by him under the provisions of this Act, no person, Officer, or Court shall be`
  line `empowered to appoint, supersede, or control any Police functionary, any Regulation Act or usage to the`
  line `contrary notwithstanding.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (68857)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Inspector-General of Police, &c.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284&sectionId=68857&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `The administration of the Police throughout the General`
  line `Police District shall be vested in an Officer to be styled the Inspector-General of Police for the Presidency`
  line `of Madras, and in such Subordinates as to the Governor in Council shall seem fit, who shall from time to`
  line `time be appointed by the Governor in Council, and may be removed by the same authority, and who shall`
  line `receive such salary as the Governor General of India in Council shall allow.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (68858)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Powers of Police, &c.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284&sectionId=68858&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `All powers not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act which up to`
  line `the passing of this Act belonged by law to the existing police authorities shall be vested in the Police`
  line `authorities appointed under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that always that no police functionary so appointed shall`
  line `possess or exercise any judicial or revenue authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (68909)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Inspector-General to be appointed a Justice of the Peace. To have the powers of a Magistrate but to exercise such powers under the orders of Government. District Superintendent may be appointed a Magistrate. In what cases he may act in that capacity`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284&sectionId=68909&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `The Inspector-General`
  line `of Police shall be appointed a Justice of the Peace; he shall also have the full powers of a Magistrate`
  line `throughout the General Police District, but shall exercise these powers subject to such orders as may from`
  line `time to time be issued by the Governor in Council. The Governor in Council may vest any District`
  line `Superintendent of Police with all or any of the powers of a Magistrate within such limits as he may deem`
  line `proper; but such Superintendent shall exercise the powers with which he shall be so invested only so far`
  line `as may be necessary for the peace, the prevention of crime, and the detection, apprehension, and detention`
  line `of offenders in order to their being brought before a Magistrate, and as far as may be necessary for the`
  line `performance of the duties assigned to him by this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (68860)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Constitution of the Force.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284&sectionId=68860&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `The entire Police establishment of the Madras Presidency shall for`
  line `the purposes of this Act be deemed to be one Police Force, and shall be formally enrolled, and shall`
  line `consist of such number of Officers and men, and shall be otherwise constituted in such manner, as shall`
  line `be from time to time ordered by the Governor in Council with the sanction of the Governor General of`
  line `India in Council.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (68861)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Inspector-General to control Force and make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284&sectionId=68861&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `The Inspector-General may from time`
  line `to time, subject to the approval of the Governor in Council, frame such orders and regulations as he shall`
  line `deem expedient, relative to the general government and distribution of the Force, the places of residence,`
  line `the classification, rank, and particular service of the members thereof; their inspection ; the description of`
  line `arms, accoutrements, and other necessaries to be furnished to them ; to the collecting and communicating`
  line `intelligence and information ; and all such other orders and regulations relative to the said Police Force as`
  line `the said Inspector-General shall, from time to time, deem expedient for preventing abuse or neglect, and`
  line `for rendering such Force efficient in the Discharge of all its duties.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (68862)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Appointment and dismissal of Police Officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284&sectionId=68862&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `The appointment of all Police Officers shall,`
  line `under such rules as the Governor in Council shall from time to time sanctions, rest with the InspectorGeneral of Police and the Deputy Superintendents, who may under such rules as aforesaid at any time`
  line `dismiss, suspend, or fine to any amount not exceeding one month’s pay, any Police Officer whom they`
  line `shall think remiss or negligent in the discharge of his duty, or otherwise unfit for the same.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (68863)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Police Officers to receive certificates of Office.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284&sectionId=68863&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `Every person so appointed shall receive on his`
  line `enrolment a certificate (A) under the seal of the Inspector-General, by virtue of which he shall be vested`
  line `with the powers, functions, and privileges of the Police Officer. Such certificate shall cease to have effect`
  line `whenever the person named in it is suspended or dismissed, or otherwise removed from employment in`
  line `the Police Force, and shall thereupon be immediately surrendered to his superior Officer, or other person`
  line `empowered to receive it.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (68864)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Police Superannuation Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284&sectionId=68864&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `There shall be deducted from the pay of every Police Officer of`
  line `a class not entitled to the benefit of the Uncovenanted Service Pension Rules, a sum after such rate as the Governor in Council shall direct, not being a greater rate than one anna in the Rupee; which sum so`
  line `deducted and also the monies accruing from stoppages from the pay of Police Officers during absence`
  line `from sickness or other cause, and fines imposed on Police Officers for misconduct, and from fines`
  line `imposed by Magistrates and other upon drunken persons, or for assaults upon Police Officers, and all`
  line `monies arising from the sale of worn or cast-off clothing, or other articles supplied for the use of the`
  line `Police, or from any other miscellaneous sources which shall be permitted by the Governor in Council,`
  line `shall from time to time be invested in such manner and in such securities as the Governor in Council may`
  line `direct, and the interest and dividends thereof, or so much of the same as shall not be required for the`
  line `purposes herein mentioned, shall be likewise in vested as aforesaid, and accumulate, so as to form a Fund`
  line `to be called “The Police Superannuation Fund”; and shall be applied from time to time to the payment of`
  line `superannuation or retiring allowances, or gratuities, under such rules as may be passed by the said`
  line `Governor in Council :`
  line `Proviso.-provided always that any Police Officer may be dismissed or removed`
  line `without superannuation allowance; and that no Police Officer shall be entitled or right to any allowance`
  line `from this Fund; or shall retain any right to a refund of any deduction made from him pay while he may`
  line `have been a Police Officer.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (68865)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Additional Police Officers employed at the cost of Individuals.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284&sectionId=68865&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `It shall be lawful for the`
  line `Inspector-General of Police, or any District Superintendent, if they shall think fit, on the application of`
  line `any person showing the necessity thereof, to depute any additional number of Police Officers to keep the`
  line `peace at any place within the General Police District, at the charge of the person making the application,`
  line `but subject to the orders of the said Inspector-General or District Superintendent and for such time as they`
  line `shall think fit; provided alays that it shall be lawful for the person on whose application such deputation`
  line `shall have been made, on giving one month’s notice in writing to the Inspector-General or District`
  line `Superintendent, to require that the Officers so appointed shall be discontinued: such person shall be`
  line `relieved from the charge of such additional force from the expiration of such notice.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (68866)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Appointment of additional Force in the neighbourhood of Railway and other works.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284&sectionId=68866&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `Whenever any Railway, Canal, or other Public work shall be carried on, or be in operation in any part of`
  line `the country, and it shall appear to the Inspector-General that the Appointment of an additional Police`
  line `Force in such neighbourhood is rendered necessary by the behaviour or reasonable apprehension of the`
  line `behaviour of the persons employed upon such work, it shall be lawful for the Inspector-General, with the`
  line `consent of the Governor in Council, to direct the employment of such additional Force, and to maintain`
  line `the same so long as such necessity shall continue; and to make orders from time to time upon the`
  line `Treasurer or other Officer having the control or custody of the Funds of any Company carrying on such`
  line `works, for the payment of the extra Force so rendered necessary as aforesaid.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (68867)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Payment of money for support of additional Police Force.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284&sectionId=68867&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `All monies paid in respect of`
  line `such additional Force ad is mentioned in the two last preceding Sections, shall be paid into a fund to be`
  line `called “The General Police Fund,” and shall be applied to the maintenance of the Police Force under such`
  line `orders as the Governor in Council may pass; and all sums of money payable under those Sections shall be`
  line `recoverable by suit in any competent Court or by distress and sale of the goods of the defaulter under the`
  line `warrant of a Magistrate.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (68868)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Special Police Officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284&sectionId=68868&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `When it shall appear that any tumult, riot, or outrage has taken place,`
  line `or may be reasonably apprehended in any place, and that the ordinary Officers appointed for preserving of`
  line `the inhabitants, and the security of property in such place, it shall be lawful for any Police Officer not`
  line `below the rank of Inspector to apply to the nearest Magistrate to appoint so many of the public or village`
  line `servants, or residents of the neighbourhood, as such Police Officer may require to act as special Police`
  line `Officers for such time and in such manner as he shall deem necessary; and it shall be the duty of such`
  line `Magistrate at once to comply with such applications.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (68869)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Powers of special Police Officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284&sectionId=68869&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `Every special Police Officer so appointed shall have the`
  line `same powers, privileges, and protection, and be liable to all such duties and penalties, and be subordinate`
  line `to the same authorities as the ordinary Officers of Police.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (68870)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Refusal to serve.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284&sectionId=68870&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `If any person being appointed a special Police Officer as aforesaid, shall`
  line `without sufficient excuse neglect or refuse to serve as such, or to obey such lawful order or direction as may be given him for the performance of his duties, he shall be liable upon conviction before a Magistrate`
  line `to a fine not exceeding fifty Rupees for such neglect, refusal, or disobedience.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (68871)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Police Officers not to resign without leave or two months’ notice.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284&sectionId=68871&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `No Police Officer shall`
  line `be at liberty to resign his office, or withdraw himself from the duties thereof, unless expressly allowed to`
  line `do so in writing by the District Superintendent; or unless he shall have given to his superior Officer two`
  line `months’ notice in writing of his intention to do so. Nor shall any such Police Officer engage in any`
  line `employment or office whatever, other than his duties under this Act, unless expressly permitted to do so`
  line `in writing under the seal of the Inspector-General.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (68872)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Unlawful assumption of Police functions, personation of Police, &c.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284&sectionId=68872&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `Farm and after the`
  line `passing of this Act, every person, not being, or having ceased to be, a duly enrolled Police Officer, who`
  line `shall unlawfully assume any function or power belonging to the Police; and who shall not forthwith`
  line `deliver up his certificate, and all the clothing, accoutrements, and appointments, and other necessaries`
  line `which may have been supplied to him for the execution of his duty; or who shall have in his possession`
  line `any distinctive article of the dress or appointment directed to be worn exclusively by the Police Force,`
  line `without being able to account satisfactorily for his possession thereof; or who shall put on the dress of any`
  line `Police Officer, or any dress designed to represent it, or to be taken for it; or who shall otherwise personate`
  line `the character of act the part of any Police Officer for any purpose whatever; shall, in addition to any other`
  line `punishment to which he may be liable for any offence committed under the assumed character, be liable`
  line `on conviction before a Magistrate to a penalty not exceeding two hundred Rupees, or to imprisonment,`
  line `with or without herd labor, for a period not exceeding six months, or both.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (68873)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Duties of Police Officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284&sectionId=68873&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `Every Police Officer shall, for all purposes in this Act contained,`
  line `be considered to be always on duty and shall have the powers of a Police Officer in every part of the`
  line `General Police District. It shall be his duty to use his best endeavours and ability to prevent all crimes,`
  line `offences, and public nuisances; to preserve the peace; to apprehend disorderly and suspicious character; to`
  line `detect and bring offenders to justice; to collect and communicate intelligence affecting the public peace;`
  line `and promptly to obey and execute all orders and warrants lawfully issued to him.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (68874)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Police Officer may arrest without warrant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284&sectionId=68874&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `It shall be the duty of every Police Officer, and he is hereby authorized, to arrest without warrant—`
  line
  line `1. Person charged with or suspected of grave crimes.—Any person who is charged on credible`
  line `information, or whom he has reasonable ground to suspect of having been concerned in any grave or`
  line `forcible crime or outrage.`
  line
  line `2. Persons charged with aggravated assault recently committed.—Any person who is charged`
  line `with committing an aggravated assault in every case in which he shall have good reason to believe`
  line `that such assault has been committed, although not in his view, and that by reason of the recent`
  line `commission of the offence a warrant could not have been issued.`
  line
  line `3. Persons committing a breach of the peace.—Any person committing, or attempting to commit,`
  line `any breach of the peace in his view, and who refuses to desist on being required thereto.`
  line
  line `4. Persons found injuring public buildings, &c.—Any person found injuring the public buildings,`
  line `roads, tanks, and water channels, or committing any offence punishable by law.`
  line .
  line
  line Proviso.---Provided
  line `always that where such offence is of a slight and petty nature, it shall not be necessary for the Police`
  line `Officer to arrest, if, from the circumstances of the case, there is no reason to apprehend that the party`
  line `will abscond.`
  line
  line `5. Vagrants and suspicious persons.—Any vagrant whom he shall find disturbing the public`
  line `peace, or whom he shall have good cause to suspect of having committed, or being about to commit a`
  line `crime; all persons whose name and residence is unknown, or whom he may find by night lying or`
  line `loitering in any high-way, road, or other place, and who, in either case, are unable to give a`
  line `satisfactory account of themselves.`
  line
  line `6. Persons assaulting Police Officer.—Any person who assaults, resists, or obstructs such Police`
  line `Officer in the execution of his duty or aids or excites others so to do.`
  line
  line `7. Persons escaping from legal custody.—All persons who, having been in legal custody, shall`
  line `have escaped therefrom.`
  line
  line `8. Persons charged with an offence, refusing to give name.—All persons who are charged with`
  line `having done any injury or damage to the person or property of another, and who refuse to give their`
  line `name and residence, or who give one which there is ground to believe to be false, may be detained`
  line `solely for the purpose of ascertaining such name and residence, with a view to future proceedings.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (68910)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Persons arrested without warrant to be taken to Station House until brought before Magistrate or bailed`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284&sectionId=68910&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `Every person taken into custody by any Police Officer, without warrant, except`
  line `persons detained for the mere purpose of ascertaining their name and residence, shall forthwith be`
  line `delivered into the custody of the Police Officer in charged of a Station House, in order that such person`
  line `may be secured until he brought before a Magistrate to be dealt with according to law, or may give bail`
  line `for his appearance before a Magistrate, if the Officer in charge shall deem it prudent to take bail as`
  line `hereinafter mentioned;`
  line
  line `Proviso.----Provided always that, where bail is not taken, the prisoner shall be`
  line `brought before a Magistrate within twenty-four hours, unless circumstances render delay unavoidable.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (68876)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Release on bail.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284&sectionId=68876&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `Whenever any person shall be brought in custody, without a warrant, to`
  line `any Station House, at a time when he cannot at one be sent before a Magistrate, and shall be charged with`
  line `any bailable offence, or with any unbailable offence of which it shall appear to the Officer in charge of`
  line `the Station House that the prisoner is falsely accused, it shall be lawful for such Police Officer to release`
  line `the accused on bail or on his own recognizance to appear before the Magistrate when required.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (68877)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Superior Officer of Police may take recognizance for appearance of prosecutor or witness.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284&sectionId=68877&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `It shall be lawful for every Police Officer in charge of a Station, or other superior Officer of`
  line `Police, to bind by recognizance any person to appear as prosecutor or as a witness before the Magistrate`
  line `by whom any grave charge in being or is about to be investigated ; and if any such prosecutor or witness`
  line `shall refuse to execute such recognizance, it shall be competent to such Officer to forward the person in`
  line `custody to the Magistrate’s Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (68878)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Condition of recognizance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284&sectionId=68878&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `Every Recognizance so taken shall be without fee or reward`
  line `and shall be conditioned for the appearance of the person there by bound before a Magistrate at such time`
  line `and place as may be required, and the time and place of appearance, and the sum thereby acknowledged,`
  line `not exceeding one thousand Rupees, shall be specified in the said recognizance, or in the condition`
  line `thereof; and the Officer taking the recognizance shall return the same forthwith to the Magistrate present`
  line `at the time and place when and where the party is bound to appear.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (68879)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title Remands.
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284&sectionId=68879&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `If from the absence of witnesses, or from any other reasonable cause, it shall`
  line `become necessary or advisable to defer the examination of any case, or the further examination of any`
  line `witnesses, it shall be lawful for any Magistrate form time to time by his warrant to remand the accused to`
  line `the custody of any Police Officer, for such time as he shall deem necessary and reasonable, not exceeding`
  line `eight clear days, to be secured in any Station House or jail or to be otherwise detained in custody as to the`
  line `said Magistrate shall appear expedient: Proviso. provided always that any such Magistrate may order`
  line `such accused party to be brought before him at any time or place before the expiration of the time for`
  line `which such accused party shall have been remanded; or may discharge such accused party on his`
  line `recognizances, with or without sureties, conditioned for his appearance at the time and place appointed`
  line `for such further examination.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (68880)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Entering drinking shops, &c. without a warrant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284&sectionId=68880&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `It shall be lawful for any Police`
  line `Officer without a warrant to enter and inspect all drinking shops gaming houses and other resorts of loose`
  line `and disorderly characters all premises of persons suspected of receiving stolen property any locality`
  line `vessel boat or conveyance in any part of which places he shall have just cause to believe that crime has`
  line `been or is about to be committed or which he reasonably suspects to contain stolen property; and then and`
  line `there to take all necessary measures for the effectual prevention and detection of crime and to take charge`
  line `of all property reasonably suspected to have been stolen and of all articles or things which may serve as`
  line `evidence of the crime supposed to have been committed.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (68881)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Inspection of weights and measures.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284&sectionId=68881&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `Every Police Officer, not below the grade of`
  line `Inspector, shall be an inspector of weights and measures, and may enter any shop or premises for the purpose of inspecting the weights and measures and instruments for weighing kept or used therein, and`
  line `may seize any weight, measure, or instrument for weighing, which he may have reason to believe is false.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (68882)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Police Officer not to receive complaints of petty offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284&sectionId=68882&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `No Police Officer shall receive`
  line `any complaint of any petty offence; or take into his custody any person brought to him accused of such`
  line `petty offences, trespass, assault, quarrelling, or the like; and it shall be lawful for any Police Officer to`
  line `refuse to receive any charge of an offence of a grave character, if he shall on enquiry made of the`
  line `complainant alone, see good grounds for doubting its truth: Proviso.- Provided always that, if the charge`
  line `be not of such a nature as under ordinary circumstances would justify the Police Officer in refusing to`
  line `receive it, the particular reasons for refusing it are to be recorded by such Officer at the time.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (68883)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Police Officers may lay informations, &c.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284&sectionId=68883&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `It shall be lawful for any Police Officer to lay`
  line `any information before the Magistrate, and to apply for summons, warrant, search warrant, or such other`
  line `legal process as may by law issue and may be expedient under the circumstances, against any person`
  line `committing an offence against any law or enactment, or against any regulation for the protection of the`
  line `Revenue, or against any person committing or falling to remove any public nuisance or unwarrantable`
  line `obstructions, keeping disorderly houses, harbouring thieves, disturbing the peace, obstructing the due`
  line `course of justice, and the like, and to prosecute such offenders up to final judgment;`
  line Proviso.-provided
  line `always that any rewards, forfeitures, and penalties, or shares of rewards, forfeitures, or penalties, which`
  line `by law are payable to informers, and all costs of prosecution which may by any enactment be awarded to`
  line `the prosecutor, shall be paid into the “General Police Fund.”`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (68884)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `All warrants &c. to be executed by Officers of the Police Force.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284&sectionId=68884&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `From and after the`
  line `passing of this Act, all summonses, warrants, search warrants, warrants of commitment for trial, or orders`
  line `for the escort and conveyance of prisoners, and all other processes issued by any Officer in any Criminal`
  line `proceeding, shall be directed and delivered to Officers of the Police alone; and such processes shall be`
  line `served and executed by them and none others.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (68885)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Warrant to be endorsed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284&sectionId=68885&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `Where any such warrant, order, or process shall be directed or`
  line `delivered to any of the said Officers, unless it be necessary for the due execution thereof that such warrant`
  line `be executed without delay, the person receiving it shall deliver the same to any Officer authorized for that`
  line `purpose, who shall take charge of it, and appoint by endorsement thereon one or more Police Officers to`
  line `execute the same, or endorse it to any other Officer for a like purpose and every Police Officer whose`
  line `name shall be so endorsed thereon shall be so endorsed thereon shall have the same powers, privileges,`
  line `and protection as if the same had originally been directed to him by name;`
  line `Proviso.--- Provided also that`
  line `every such process shall be executed with all secrecy and dispatch; and shall have full force in any part of`
  line `the Madras Presidency except within the limits of the Supreme Court, without further formality or local`
  line `endorsement; and that all Police authorities shall every where be assisting in the execution of such`
  line process.
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (68886)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Service of summonses, &c.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284&sectionId=68886&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `Every summons, notice, or other Criminal process may be`
  line `served on the party named personally, or be left with some adult male member of his family, or a copy`
  line `thereof may be affixed on some adult male member of his family, or a copy thereof party failing or`
  line `neglecting to obey such summons or notice duly served, shall be liable, at the discretion of the Magistrate`
  line `or Court that issued the process, to a penalty not exceeding ten Rupees unless such person shall be able to`
  line `prove that he was prevented by unavoidable accident or other satisfactory cause from obeying such`
  line `summons, notice, or the like.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (68887)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Warrant without summons.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284&sectionId=68887&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `A Magistrate may, without issuing any summons, forthwith`
  line `issue his warrant to bring before him any person charged with an offence cognizable by him, or whose`
  line `attendance it may for any reason be necessary to enforce, whenever it shall appear probable that such`
  line `person will not attend unless compelled so to do`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (68888)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Notification of substance of warrant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284&sectionId=68888&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `A Police Officer executing a warrant of arrest shall`
  line `notify the substance of the warrant, and if required so to do shall show the warrant.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (68889)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `Warrant how to be executed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284&sectionId=68889&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `In making an arrest, the Police Officer executing the`
  line `warrant shall actually touch or confine the body of the person to be arrested, unless there be a submission`
  line `to the custody by ward or action.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (68890)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `No unnecessary restraint.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284&sectionId=68890&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `After arrest the prisoner shall not be subjected to any more`
  line `restraint than such as may be necessary to prevent his escape.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (68891)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 39
  title `Breaking of outer door of window.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284&sectionId=68891&sectionno=39&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `Any Police Officer authorized by a warrant to arrest`
  line `a person accused of any offence for which a warrant may issue on complaint, may break open any outer`
  line `or inner door or window of a dwelling house, whether that of the person accused or of any other person,`
  line `in order to execute such warrant, if, after notification of his authority and purpose, and demand of`
  line `admittance duly made, he cannot otherwise obtain admittance`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (68892)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 40
  title `Breaking open Zenanah or female apartment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284&sectionId=68892&sectionno=40&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `If information be received that a person`
  line `accused of any offence for which a warrant may issue, has concealed himself in a Zenanah or female`
  line `apartment in the actual occupancy of women, the Officer employed to execute the warrant shall take such`
  line `precautions as may be necessary to prevent the escape of the accused; and if such person shall not deliver`
  line `himself up, the Police Officer authorized to execute the warrant, may break open the Zenanah, and`
  line `execute the process intrusted to him giving notice at the same time to any woman in the Zenanah that she`
  line `is at liberty to withdraw.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (68893)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 41
  title `Party arrested to be brought immediately to the authority mentioned in the warrant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284&sectionId=68893&sectionno=41&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `After arrest made, the Police Officer executing the warrant shall without unnecessary delay bring the`
  line `person arrested before the Magistrate or other authority described in the warrant.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (68894)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 42
  title `No threat or promise, to compel disclosure by party arrested.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284&sectionId=68894&sectionno=42&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `No Police Officer shall`
  line `offer to the person arrested any in ducement, by threat or promise or otherwise, to make any disclosure.`
  line `But no Police Officer shall prevent the person arrested, by any caution or otherwise, from making any`
  line `disclosure which he may be disposed to make of his own free will.`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (68895)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 43
  title `Police Officer may require assistance. Penalty for refusal to assist.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284&sectionId=68895&sectionno=43&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `If any Police Officer`
  line `shall at any time find himself unable to effect an arrest, it shall be lawful for him to require any and every`
  line `person present to assist and aid him in making the arrest; and any person who shall refuse or neglect to`
  line `comply with such requisition, shall be liable, on conviction before a Magistrate, to a fine not exceeding`
  line `fifty Rupees, or to imprisonment for a period not exceeding three months, or both.`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (68896)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 44
  title `Penalties for neglect of duty &c.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284&sectionId=68896&sectionno=44&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `Every Police-officer who shall be guilty of any violation`
  line `of duty or wilful breach of any lawful orders and regulations not punishable under Section X of this Act ;`
  line `or who shall cease to perform the duties of his office without leave, or without having given two months’`
  line `notice as provided by this enactment, or engage without authority in any employment other than his`
  line `Police duty, or who shall maliciously and without probable cause prefer any false, vexatious or frivolous`
  line `charge or information against any individual, or who shall knowingly and wilfully and with evil intent`
  line `exceed his powers, or shall be guilty of any wilful and culpable neglect of duty, in not bringing any`
  line `person who shall be in his custody without a warrant before a Magistrate as provided by law, or who shall`
  line `offer any unwarrantable personal violence to any person in his custody, shall be liable, on conviction,`
  line `before a Magistrate, to a penalty not exceeding three months pay, or to imprisonment with or without hard`
  line `labour not exceeding three months or both.`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (68897)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 45
  title `Penalty for receiving unauthorized fees, &c.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284&sectionId=68897&sectionno=45&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `Any Police-officer who shall on any pretext,`
  line `or under any circumstances, directly or indirectly collect or receive any fee, gratuity, diet-money`
  line `allowance or recompense, other than he may be duly authorized by the Inspector-General or other Officer`
  line `acting under his order to collect or receive shall, on conviction before a Magistrate be liable to a penalty`
  line `not exceeding six months’ pay, or to imprisonment, with or without hard labour, not exceeding six`
  line `months or both.`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (68898)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 46
  title `Penalty for extortion, &c.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284&sectionId=68898&sectionno=46&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `Any Police Officer who shall directly or indirectly extort,`
  line `extract, seek, or obtain any bribe or unauthorized reward or consideration, by any illegal threat or`
  line `pretence, or for doing or omitting or delaying to do any act which it may be his duty to do or to cause to`
  line `be done, or for withholding or delaying any information which he is bound to afford or to communicate,`
  line `or who shall attempt to commit any of the offences above said, or shall be guilty of cowardice, shall be`
  line `liable, upon conviction before a Magistrate, to a fine not exceeding twelve months pay, or to`
  line `imprisonment with or without hard labor not exceeding twelve months, or both:`
  line
  line `Proviso.---Provided always that nothing in the three last preceding sections shall be deemed to preclude the Magistrate from`
  line `committing for trial any cases of this nature too serious for his cognizance.`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (68899)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 47
  title `Penalty for obstructing a Police Officer in the execution of his duty.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284&sectionId=68899&sectionno=47&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `If any person shall`
  line `assault or resist any Police Officer in the execution of his duty; or shall aid or incite any other person so to`
  line `do; or shall maliciously and without probable cause prefer any false or frivolous charge against any`
  line `Police-officer, such person shall, on conviction of such offence before any Magistrate, be liable to a fine`
  line `not exceeding fifty rupees, or to imprisonment, with or without hard labour, not exceeding three months,`
  line `or both.`
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (68900)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 48
  title `Certain duties of Police Officers within the limits of Towns. Obstructions and nuisances in roads.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284&sectionId=68900&sectionno=48&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `Any person who in any street, road, thoroughfare, or passage, within the limits of`
  line `any Town, commits any of the following offences, to the obstruction, inconvenience, annoyance, risk, or`
  line `damage of the residents and passengers, shall, on conviction before a Magistrate, be liable to a fine not`
  line `exceeding fifty Rupees, or to imprisonment not exceeding eight days; and it shall be lawful for any Police`
  line `Officer to take into custody without warrant any person who within view commits any such offence.`
  line
  line `First. slaughtering cattle, furious riding, &c.— Any person who shall slaughter any cattle or clean`
  line `any carcase in the streets; any person riding or driving any cattle recklessly and furiously, or training`
  line `or breaking any horse or other cattle on or near any public road, to the danger of the passers:`
  line
  line `Second. Cruelty to animals.—Any person who wantonly or cruelly abuses or tortures any animal:`
  line
  line `Third. Obstructing passengers.—Any person who shall keep any cattle, or conveyance of any`
  line `kind standing in any road or street longer than is required for loading or unloading, or for taking up or`
  line `setting down passengers; or who shall leave any conveyance in such a manner as to cause`
  line `inconvenience or danger to the public.`
  line
  line `Fourth. Exposing goods for sale on road.—Any person exposing goods for sale on the road so as`
  line `to obstruct passengers:`
  line
  line `Fifth. Throwing dirt into street.—Any person who throws or lays down any dirt, filth, rubbish, or`
  line `any stones or building materials; or who constructs any pial, cowshed, stable, or the like within the`
  line `bounds of any thoroughfare; or who causes any offensive matter to run from any house, factory, dung`
  line `heap, or the like into the street:`
  line
  line `Sixth. Being Found drunk in any thoroughfare.—Any person found in any thoroughfare drunk`
  line `and riotous or incapable of taking care of himself.`
  line
  line `Seventh. Indecent exposure person.—Any person who willfully and indecently exposes his`
  line `person, or any offensive deformity or disease, or commits nuisance by easing himself in or by the side`
  line `of, or near any public street or thoroughfare; or by bathing or washing in any tank or reservoir, not`
  line `being a place set apart for that purpose:`
  line
  line `Eighth. Neglect to protect dangerous places.—Any person who neglects to fence in or duly to`
  line `protect any well, tank, or other dangerous place or structure.`
obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (68901)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 49
  title `Regulation of public processions, &c., and of carriages and persons at places of public resort.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284&sectionId=68901&sectionno=49&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `The Superintendent and Superior Officers of Police may,`
  line `as occasion requires, direct the conduct of all assemblies and processions in the public roads, streets, or`
  line `thoroughfares, prescribe the routes by which, and the times at which such processions may pass ; keep`
  line `order in the public roads, streets, thoroughfares, ghauts, and landing places, and all other places of public`
  line `resort, and prevent obstructions on the occasion of such assemblies and processions and in the`
  line `neighbourhood of places of worship during the time of public worship, and in any case when the roads,`
  line `streets or, thoroughfares, ghauts or landing places, may be thronged, or may be liable to be obstructed ;`
  line `they may also regulate the use of music in the streets, on the occasion of native festivals and ceremonies;`
  line `and may direct all crowds of twelve or more persons to disperse, when they have direct all crowds of`
  line `twelve or more persons to disperse, when they have reason to apprehend any breach of the peace ; and`
  line `every person opposing, or not obeying the orders so issued as aforesaid, or violating the conditions of`
  line `such license, shall be liable to a fine not exceeding one hundred Rupees. Provided always that nothing in this Section contained shall be deemed to interfere with the general control of the Magistrate over such`
  line matters.
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (68902)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 50
  title Jurisdiction.
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284&sectionId=68902&sectionno=50&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `In all cases of convictions under this Act, the Magistrate trying the case shall be`
  line `restrained within the limits of his ordinary jurisdiction as to the amount of fine or imprisonment he may`
  line `inflict ; Proviso provided always that such charges against Police Officers above the rank of a Private`
  line `shall only be adjudicated on by European functionaries, and that Village Watchers alone shall be liable to`
  line `conviction by Heads of Villages.`
obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (68903)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 51
  title `Liability to prosecution for higher penalties not affected.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284&sectionId=68903&sectionno=51&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `Nothing contained in this Act shall`
  line `be construed to prevent any person from being prosecuted for any offence made punishable on conviction`
  line `by this Act ; or to prevent any person from being liable under any other law, Regulation, or Act to any`
  line `other or higher penalty or punishment than is provided for such offence by this Act. Proviso.- Provided`
  line `always that no person shall be punished twice for the same offence.`
obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (68904)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 52
  title `Levy of fines.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284&sectionId=68904&sectionno=52&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `All fines and penalties imposed, and all sums of money recoverable under the`
  line `authority of this Act, may, in case of non-payment thereof, be levied by distress and sale of the goods and`
  line `chattels of the offender by warrant of the Magistrate, in manner provided by Act II of 1839.th`
obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (68905)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 53
  title `Limitation of action.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284&sectionId=68905&sectionno=53&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `All actions and prosecutions against any person, which may be lawfully`
  line `brought for any thing done or intended to be done, under the provisions of this Act, or under the general`
  line `Police powers hereby given, shall be commenced within three months after the act complained of shall`
  line `have been committed, and not otherwise; and notice in writing of such action and of the cause thereof,`
  line `shall be given to the defendant; or to the Superintendent or other superior officer of the district in which`
  line `the act was committed, one month at least before the commencement of the action; and no plaintiff shall`
  line `recover in any such action, if tender of sufficient amends shall have been made before such action`
  line `brought, or if a sufficient sum of money shall have been paid into Court after such action, brought by or`
  line `on behalf of the defendant; and though a decree shall be given for the plaintiff in any such action, such`
  line `plaintiff shall not have cost against the defendant unless the Judge, before whom the trial shall be, shall`
  line `certify his approbation of the action:`
  line `Proviso. provided always that no action shall, in any case lie where`
  line `such officers shall have been prosecuted criminally for the same act.`
obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (68906)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 54
  title `Plea that act was done under a warrant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284&sectionId=68906&sectionno=54&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `When any action, prosecution, or proceeding shall`
  line `be brought against any Police-officer for any act done by him in such capacity, it shall be lawful for him`
  line `to plead that such act was done by him under the authority of a warrant issued by a Magistrate; and such`
  line `plea shall be proved by the production of the warrant directing the act and purporting to be signed by a`
  line `Magistrate. And the defendant shall, thereupon, be entitled to a decree in his favour, notwithstanding any`
  line `defect of jurisdiction in such Magistrate. And no proof of the signature of such official shall be necessary,`
  line `unless the Court shall see reason to doubt it being genuine: Proviso.- Provided always that any remedy`
  line `which the party may have against the authority issuing such warrant shall remain entire.`
obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_55:
  sectionId (68907)
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 55
  title `Operation of Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284&sectionId=68907&sectionno=55&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00091_185924_1661923291284
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line `This Act shall take effect in any and every such District as the Governor in`
  line `Council shall by notification published in the Official Gazette.`
obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes:
  string
  line
